<br>
You know, if you think about it, making Shock of Firey Blades conjuration based really is a benefit to mages in a big way.  It allows us to specialize in something almost all our heavily used spells use.  There is no more need to decide &quot;what do I do more of?  Nuking or summoning?&quot;  All you do is &quot;summon&quot; DD, items, or people.  Kudos to Verant for the silent &quot;upgrade.&quot; <p>Dalynia Aziz<br>
Arch Mage of Felwithe<br>
Innoruuk Server<br>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=28865"><i>profile</i></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/usuzannadreamingheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>SuzannaDreamingheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 36<br> <font color=#333333>(7/9/02 3:48:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm31.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=23.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: What did you Specialize in?</span><hr size=1> &quot;At level 60 our best fire and magic nukes are both conjuration, and our main utility spells, Mod Rod (1 or 2), and CotH are both conjuration based.&quot; - Dalynia<br>
<br>
You would need to define 'best' here very carefully. As far as nukes go, I would contend your statement to be entirely incorrect.<br>
<br>
As stated on the Spells forum in the thread about Sirocco vs SOFB, Sirocco has in practice a DPM of 4.42 for an Evocation Mage, which includes resists. From theory alone, Seukors, also evocation, for an Evocation Mage, with the standard damage bracer, has a DPM of 4.40, but this is 'perfect', and would be reduced in practice by resists.<br>
<br>
By comparison, SOFB, for a Conjuration Mage, with the standard damage bracer, has a DPM of 4.14, but this is 'perfect', and would be reduced in practice by resists.<br>
<br>
Yes, SOFB is a simple DD so requires far less skill to use than Sirocco or Seukors, but in damage output terms, it is considerably inferior to the best Evocation nukes. Add to this that you use Scintillation in AE groups (evocation), and Sigil for fast casts (also evocation), and it should be clear to anyone other than the most blinkered, for nuking alone, Evocation &gt; Conjuration, even at 60.<br>
<br>
The other factors, tho, I'd agree with, so overall, if you raid more, conjuration is still the better choice, for all the well known reasons. But to me, since I style myself a damage dealer, they are less important, so I remain Evocation.<br>
<br>
&quot;I can't see specializing in conjuration before 60, however.&quot; - Dalynia<br>
<br>
This I agree with. Before 60, unless you are a heavy raider, stick with evocation if this is the way you play.<br>
<br>
